msgid "2.14.2 (2017-05-10)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../HISTORY.md:730
msgid ""
"Changed a less-than to an equal-to and an or in the dependency markers to "
"widen compatibility with older setuptools releases."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../HISTORY.md:734
msgid "2.14.1 (2017-05-09)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../HISTORY.md:738
msgid ""
"Changed the dependency markers to widen compatibility with older pip "
"releases."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../HISTORY.md:742
msgid "2.14.0 (2017-05-09)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../HISTORY.md:746
msgid ""
"It is now possible to pass `no_proxy` as a key to the `proxies` dictionary "
"to provide handling similar to the `NO_PROXY` environment variable."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../HISTORY.md:749
msgid ""
"When users provide invalid paths to certificate bundle files or directories "
"Requests now raises `IOError`, rather than failing at the time of the HTTPS "
"request with a fairly inscrutable certificate validation error."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../HISTORY.md:753
msgid ""
"The behavior of `SessionRedirectMixin` was slightly altered. "
"`resolve_redirects` will now detect a redirect by calling "
"`get_redirect_target(response)` instead of directly querying `Response."
"is_redirect` and `Response.headers['location']`. Advanced users will be able "
"to process malformed redirects more easily."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../HISTORY.md:758
msgid ""
"Changed the internal calculation of elapsed request time to have higher "
"resolution on Windows."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../HISTORY.md:760
msgid ""
"Added `win_inet_pton` as conditional dependency for the `[socks]` extra on "
"Windows with Python 2.7."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../HISTORY.md:762
msgid ""
"Changed the proxy bypass implementation on Windows: the proxy bypass check "
"doesn't use forward and reverse DNS requests anymore"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../HISTORY.md:764
msgid ""
"URLs with schemes that begin with `http` but are not `http` or `https` no "
"longer have their host parts forced to lowercase."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../HISTORY.md:769
msgid ""
"Much improved handling of non-ASCII `Location` header values in redirects. "
"Fewer `UnicodeDecodeErrors` are encountered on Python 2, and Python 3 now "
"correctly understands that Latin-1 is unlikely to be the correct encoding."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../HISTORY.md:773
msgid ""
"If an attempt to `seek` file to find out its length fails, we now "
"appropriately handle that by aborting our content-length calculations."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../HISTORY.md:776
msgid ""
"Restricted `HTTPDigestAuth` to only respond to auth challenges made on 4XX "
"responses, rather than to all auth challenges."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../HISTORY.md:778
msgid "Fixed some code that was firing `DeprecationWarning` on Python 3.6."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../HISTORY.md:779
msgid ""
"The dismayed person emoticon (`/o\\\\`) no longer has a big head. I'm sure "
"this is what you were all worrying about most."
msgstr ""

