msgid "Updated bundled certifi to 2017.4.17."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../HISTORY.md:790
msgid "2.13.0 (2017-01-24)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../HISTORY.md:792
msgid "**Features**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../HISTORY.md:794
msgid ""
"Only load the `idna` library when we've determined we need it. This will "
"save some memory for users."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../HISTORY.md:799
msgid "Updated bundled urllib3 to 1.20."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../HISTORY.md:800
msgid "Updated bundled idna to 2.2."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../HISTORY.md:803
msgid "2.12.5 (2017-01-18)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../HISTORY.md:807
msgid ""
"Fixed an issue with JSON encoding detection, specifically detecting big-"
"endian UTF-32 with BOM."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../HISTORY.md:811
msgid "2.12.4 (2016-12-14)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../HISTORY.md:815
msgid ""
"Fixed regression from 2.12.2 where non-string types were rejected in the "
"basic auth parameters. While support for this behaviour has been re-added, "
"the behaviour is deprecated and will be removed in the future."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../HISTORY.md:821
msgid "2.12.3 (2016-12-01)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../HISTORY.md:825
msgid ""
"Fixed regression from v2.12.1 for URLs with schemes that begin with "
"\"http\". These URLs have historically been processed as though they were "
"HTTP-schemed URLs, and so have had parameters added. This was removed in "
"v2.12.2 in an overzealous attempt to resolve problems with IDNA-encoding "
"those URLs. This change was reverted: the other fixes for IDNA-encoding have "
"been judged to be sufficient to return to the behaviour Requests had before "
"v2.12.0."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../HISTORY.md:834
msgid "2.12.2 (2016-11-30)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../HISTORY.md:838
msgid ""
"Fixed several issues with IDNA-encoding URLs that are technically invalid "
"but which are widely accepted. Requests will now attempt to IDNA-encode a "
"URL if it can but, if it fails, and the host contains only ASCII characters, "
"it will be passed through optimistically. This will allow users to opt-in to "
"using IDNA2003 themselves if they want to, and will also allow technically "
"invalid but still common hostnames."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../HISTORY.md:845
msgid ""
"Fixed an issue where URLs with leading whitespace would raise "
"`InvalidSchema` errors."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../HISTORY.md:847
msgid ""
"Fixed an issue where some URLs without the HTTP or HTTPS schemes would still "
"have HTTP URL preparation applied to them."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../HISTORY.md:849
msgid "Fixed an issue where Unicode strings could not be used in basic auth."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../HISTORY.md:851
msgid ""
"Fixed an issue encountered by some Requests plugins where constructing a "
"Response object would cause `Response.content` to raise an `AttributeError`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../HISTORY.md:856
msgid "2.12.1 (2016-11-16)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../HISTORY.md:860
msgid ""
"Updated setuptools 'security' extra for the new PyOpenSSL backend in urllib3."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../HISTORY.md:865
msgid "Updated bundled urllib3 to 1.19.1."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../HISTORY.md:868
msgid "2.12.0 (2016-11-15)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../HISTORY.md:872
msgid ""
"Updated support for internationalized domain names from IDNA2003 to "
"IDNA2008. This updated support is required for several forms of IDNs and is "
"mandatory for .de domains."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../HISTORY.md:875
msgid ""
"Much improved heuristics for guessing content lengths: Requests will no "
"longer read an entire `StringIO` into memory."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../HISTORY.md:877
msgid ""
"Much improved logic for recalculating `Content-Length` headers for "
"`PreparedRequest` objects."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../HISTORY.md:879
msgid ""
"Improved tolerance for file-like objects that have no `tell` method but do "
"have a `seek` method."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../HISTORY.md:881
msgid ""
"Anything that is a subclass of `Mapping` is now treated like a dictionary by "
"the `data=` keyword argument."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../HISTORY.md:883
msgid ""
"Requests now tolerates empty passwords in proxy credentials, rather than "
"stripping the credentials."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../HISTORY.md:885
msgid ""
"If a request is made with a file-like object as the body and that request is "
"redirected with a 307 or 308 status code, Requests will now attempt to "
"rewind the body object so it can be replayed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../HISTORY.md:891
msgid ""
"When calling `response.close`, the call to `close` will be propagated "
"through to non-urllib3 backends."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../HISTORY.md:893
msgid ""
"Fixed issue where the `ALL_PROXY` environment variable would be preferred "
"over scheme-specific variables like `HTTP_PROXY`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../HISTORY.md:895
msgid ""
"Fixed issue where non-UTF8 reason phrases got severely mangled by falling "
"back to decoding using ISO 8859-1 instead."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../HISTORY.md:897
msgid ""
"Fixed a bug where Requests would not correctly correlate cookies set when "
"using custom Host headers if those Host headers did not use the native "
"string type for the platform."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../HISTORY.md:903
msgid "Updated bundled urllib3 to 1.19."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../HISTORY.md:904
msgid "Updated bundled certifi certs to 2016.09.26."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../HISTORY.md:907
msgid "2.11.1 (2016-08-17)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../HISTORY.md:911
msgid ""
"Fixed a bug when using `iter_content` with `decode_unicode=True` for "
"streamed bodies would raise `AttributeError`. This bug was introduced in "
"2.11."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../HISTORY.md:914
msgid ""
"Strip Content-Type and Transfer-Encoding headers from the header block when "
"following a redirect that transforms the verb from POST/PUT to GET."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../HISTORY.md:919
msgid "2.11.0 (2016-08-08)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../HISTORY.md:923
msgid "Added support for the `ALL_PROXY` environment variable."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../HISTORY.md:924
msgid ""
"Reject header values that contain leading whitespace or newline characters "
"to reduce risk of header smuggling."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../HISTORY.md:929
msgid ""
"Fixed occasional `TypeError` when attempting to decode a JSON response that "
"occurred in an error case. Now correctly returns a `ValueError`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../HISTORY.md:932
msgid ""
"Requests would incorrectly ignore a non-CIDR IP address in the `NO_PROXY` "
"environment variables: Requests now treats it as a specific IP."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../HISTORY.md:935
msgid ""
"Fixed a bug when sending JSON data that could cause us to encounter obscure "
"OpenSSL errors in certain network conditions (yes, really)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../HISTORY.md:937
msgid ""
"Added type checks to ensure that `iter_content` only accepts integers and "
"`None` for chunk sizes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../HISTORY.md:939
msgid ""
"Fixed issue where responses whose body had not been fully consumed would "
"have the underlying connection closed but not returned to the connection "
"pool, which could cause Requests to hang in situations where the "
"`HTTPAdapter` had been configured to use a blocking connection pool."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../HISTORY.md:947
msgid "Updated bundled urllib3 to 1.16."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../HISTORY.md:948
msgid ""
"Some previous releases accidentally accepted non-strings as acceptable "
"header values. This release does not."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../HISTORY.md:952
msgid "2.10.0 (2016-04-29)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../HISTORY.md:954
msgid "**New Features**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../HISTORY.md:956
msgid ""
"SOCKS Proxy Support! (requires PySocks; `$ pip install requests[socks]`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../HISTORY.md:961
msgid "Updated bundled urllib3 to 1.15.1."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../HISTORY.md:964
msgid "2.9.2 (2016-04-29)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../HISTORY.md:968
msgid ""
"Change built-in CaseInsensitiveDict (used for headers) to use OrderedDict as "
"its underlying datastore."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../HISTORY.md:973
msgid "Don't use redirect\\_cache if allow\\_redirects=False"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../HISTORY.md:974
msgid ""
"When passed objects that throw exceptions from `tell()`, send them via "
"chunked transfer encoding instead of failing."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../HISTORY.md:976
msgid "Raise a ProxyError for proxy related connection issues."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../HISTORY.md:979
msgid "2.9.1 (2015-12-21)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../HISTORY.md:983
msgid ""
"Resolve regression introduced in 2.9.0 that made it impossible to send "
"binary strings as bodies in Python 3."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../HISTORY.md:985
msgid ""
"Fixed errors when calculating cookie expiration dates in certain locales."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../HISTORY.md:990
msgid "Updated bundled urllib3 to 1.13.1."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../HISTORY.md:993
msgid "2.9.0 (2015-12-15)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../HISTORY.md:995
msgid "**Minor Improvements** (Backwards compatible)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../HISTORY.md:997
msgid ""
"The `verify` keyword argument now supports being passed a path to a "
"directory of CA certificates, not just a single-file bundle."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../HISTORY.md:999
msgid "Warnings are now emitted when sending files opened in text mode."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../HISTORY.md:1000
msgid ""
"Added the 511 Network Authentication Required status code to the status code "
"registry."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../HISTORY.md:1005
msgid ""
"For file-like objects that are not sought to the very beginning, we now send "
"the content length for the number of bytes we will actually read, rather "
"than the total size of the file, allowing partial file uploads."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../HISTORY.md:1009
msgid ""
"When uploading file-like objects, if they are empty or have no obvious "
"content length we set `Transfer-Encoding: chunked` rather than `Content-"
"Length: 0`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../HISTORY.md:1012
msgid ""
"We correctly receive the response in buffered mode when uploading chunked "
"bodies."
